I'm still seeing this pretty frequently, so I want to reiterate. "Coins" and "Tokens" are not interchangeable.  Coin = Has its own blockchain. i.e. PINK, BTC, LTC, ETH, etc.  Token = Rides another coin's blockchain. i.e. ERC20, XCP token, etc (most ICOs fall under this category)
